'''Dedicated Music Award''' ([[Vietnamese language|Vietnamese]]: ''Giải thưởng Âm nhạc Cống hiến'') is an annual music award presented by ''{{illm|Sports and Culture (newspaper)|lt=Sports and Culture|vi|Thể thao & Văn hóa}}'', a prestigious entertaining newspaper in [[Viet Nam]], to recognize the discoveries and creations contributed to the richness and development of Viet Nam pop music life. This award is considered as an "[[Grammy Award]]" in Vietnamese music.<ref name="grammy">[http://dantri.com.vn/c23/s23-567384/giai-am-nhac-cong-hien-huong-toi-mot-grammy-cua-viet-nam.htm Giải âm nhạc Cống hiến hướng tới một "Grammy" của Việt Nam?]</ref><ref>[http://conghien.thethaovanhoa.vn/chitiet/c478n20120511091146298.htm Nhìn Cống hiến, thấy sướng!]. ''Sports and Culture''</ref><ref>[http://conghien.thethaovanhoa.vn/chitiet/c478n20130321081246378.htm Mong "Cống hiến" sẽ thành "Grammy Việt Nam"] ''Sports and Culture''.</ref> The first ceremony was held in 2005, with the original name "Pre-Dedicated Music Award".<ref>[http://conghien.thethaovanhoa.vn/danhsach/c483.htm Lịch sử giải thưởng âm nhạc cống hiến]. ''Sports and Culture''</ref>

