"''He fought for the Confederacy and with [[Quantrill's Raiders]]. After the war, he rode with Jesse & Frank James and [[Cole Younger]] over 100 years ago. A $50,000 reward was offered for him dead or alive; since they could not capture him, he was later pardoned by several governors with his promise that he would lead an exemplary life, which he did during his last 20 years, in Memphis.'"<ref>from the tombstone of Kit Dalton at Elmwood Cemetery, Memphis, Tennessee</ref>
