'''Monteith and Rand''' were a comedy team who had their own [[Broadway theatre|Broadway]] show at the [[Booth Theater]] in 1979, produced by [[James Lipton]], after a successful off-Broadway run.<ref>{{cite book|first= Thomas S.|last= Hischak|year= 2001|title= American Theatre: a Chronicle of Comedy and Drama, 1969–2000|location= Oxford; New York|publisher= Oxford University Press|page=141|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=1aSM__nVScAC&pg=PA141&dq=%22Monteith+and+Rand%22&hl=en&sa=X&ei=BWv3VMDdH5fVoAT5iIH4Bg&ved=0CDkQ6AEwBg#v=onepage&q=%22Monteith%20and%20Rand%22&f=false|isbn=0-19-512347-6}}</ref> Suzanne Rand and [[John Monteith (Improv)|John Monteith]] were graduates of [[The Second City|Second City]]; Suzanne was in the famed company that included [[John Belushi]] and [[Brian Doyle  Murray]] in [[Chicago, Illinois|Chicago]], and John performed with [[John Candy]], [[Dan Aykroyd]] and [[Gilda Radner]] in [[Toronto]].{{citation needed|date=March 2015}} Monteith and Rand lived in [[New York City]] where they taught and performed.{{citation needed|date=March 2015}}

John Monteith died on 16 January 2018 in [[Jersey City, New Jersey]].<ref>http://www.theintell.com/OBITUARIES/20180124/JOHN-MONTEITH</ref>

