'''Sedat Bornovalı''' (born 31 May 1970 in [[Istanbul]]) is an art historian ([[PhD]]), interpreter and professional tourist guide in [[Italian language|Italian]], [[English language|English]] and [[Turkish language|Turkish]].
As an art historian, Dr. Bornovali has contributed to several publications and projects.<ref>{{cite news|title=100 Highlights of Turkish Architecture|url=http://www.zaman.com.tr/haber.do?haberno=878445&title=iste-turkiyenin-100-mimar%EE-saheseri&haberSayfa=0|accessdate=5 December 2011|newspaper=[[Zaman (newspaper)|Zaman]]|date=9 August 2009|language=Turkish}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://anadoluselcuklumimarisi.com/ekip.asp|title=Inventory of Anatolian Selçuk buildings|editor=|autore=|accessdate=5 December 2011}}</ref> As a tour guide and interpreter he has served several religious leaders, including [[Pope Benedict XVI]],<ref>{{cite news|url=http://archiviostorico.corriere.it/2006/dicembre/02/Mufti_guardava_non_osato_interrompere_co_9_061202062.shtml|title=Mufti mi guardava ma non ho osato interrompere Sua Santità|editor=|last=Elisabetta |first=Rosaspina|newspaper=[[Corriere della Sera]] |accessdate=24 October 2013|date=2 December 2006|language=Italian|trans-title=The Mufti was looking at me but I did not dare to stop His Holiness}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.life.com/search/?q0=sedat+bornovali |title=Pope Benedict XVI with Dr. Sedat Bornovalı during his visit at the Blue Mosque|editor=|work=[[Life (magazine)|Life]] |accessdate=5 December 2011}}</ref><ref>[[Pope Benedict XVI]] with Dr. Sedat Bornovalı during his visit at the [[Sultan Ahmed Mosque|Blue Mosque]] and [[Hagia Sophia]] in [[Istanbul]].{{cite web|title=Getty Images Search|url=http://www.gettyimages.com/Search/Search.aspx?contractUrl=2&language=en-US&family=editorial&p=sedat+bornovali&assetType=image|work=Getty Images|publisher=Getty Images News|accessdate=5 December 2011}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|title=Pope Visits The Blue Mosque|url=http://www.cbsnews.com/video/watch/?id=2220362n|publisher=CBS News|accessdate=5 December 2011|date=30 November 2006}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|title=Pope Benedict second Pope in history to visit a mosque / protests continue against visit|url=http://www.itnsource.com/sho